  "riddle": "1. Unearth the ballad that ponders what might have been — seek the date this musical tale graced the airwaves.\n\n2. Within melodies, a familiar refrain echoes. How many artists' lyrics does the tune \"2002\" borrow from?\n\n3. From your last find, reduce that number to a single digit — what is its digital root?\n\n4. An invention that captured sounds, yet fell from grace — discover the year this early recording device was retired.\n\n5. Journey to a Serbian monastery with a name that whispers of serenity. How high is this sacred place above sea level?\n\n6. In a world where tunes are sold, what year saw the peak of this industry’s sales reach their zenith?\n\n7. What do travelers think of this page, denoting its quality — what star rating do they give to this musical milestone?\n\n8. Enter the land where harmony thrives — what is the number of inhabitants in this diverse southeast Asian nation?\n\n9. Now, apply a simple transformation: what do you get when you sum the digits of that population figure?\n\n10. Seek the chart that paved the way for digital auditory sensations. In which month and year did it first emerge?\n\n11. This label not only produces melodies but also boasts a headquarters recognized in name and location — uncover its title.\n\n12. How many vowels are hidden within that name, revealing its lyrical charm?\n\n13. Find where the vibrant genre known for its city-inspired themes finds its roots. What cultural origins are attributed to it?\n\n14. Ascend to a place boasting prosperity and tranquility. When the sun shone bright on January 1, 1999, how long did its rays linger, measured in seconds?\n\n15. Dive into the realm of chill beats, where different influences converge. Count the stylistic origins that define this laid-back genre.\n\n16. A question for the musically astute: after your previous total, what is the next prime number that follows?\n\n17. This platform connects creators with fans, born in Oakland. In which year did it open